==Personal life==
Winkler has been married to Stacey Winkler (née Furstman)<ref>{{cite web|last=Boughton |first=Victoria |url=http://www.people.com/people/archive/article/0,,20134304,00.html |title=Happy Daze - Personal Success, Where Are They Now?, Henry Winkler |publisher=People.com |date=2001-05-07 |accessdate=2014-12-09}}</ref> since May 5, 1978; with her, he has two children, Zoe Emily (b. 1980), a pre-school teacher,<ref name=LAConf-Daughter-Zoe-2009>{{cite news|last1=Preskill|first1=Adam|title=The Fonz's Daughter Chooses Her Own Path|url=http://la-confidential-magazine.com/living/articles/class-act|accessdate=20 April 2015|work=[[Los Angeles Confidential]]|date=October 2009}}</ref><ref name=NYTimes-Daughter-Zoe-Wed-2009>{{cite news|last1=Segre|first1=Francesca|title=Vows: Zoe Winkler and Robert Reinis|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2009/07/19/fashion/weddings/19VOWS.html|accessdate=20 April 2015|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=18 July 2009}}</ref> and [[Max Winkler (director)|Max Daniel]] (b. August 18, 1983), a director. Winkler also has a stepson, Jed Weitzman, from Stacey's previous marriage with [[Howard Weitzman]].

Winkler is a cousin of actor [[Richard Belzer]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvguide.com/PhotoGallery/Surprising-Celebrity-Family-1073313/1073326 |title=Henry Winkler Pictures, Richard Belzer Photos - Photo Gallery: Surprising Celebrity Family Ties |last= |first= |date= |website= |publisher=[[TV Guide]] |accessdate=October 31, 2014}}</ref> Winkler is the godfather of [[Bryce Dallas Howard]], daughter of ''[[Happy Days]]'' co-star [[Ron Howard]]. Henry was the 9th King of the Bacchus, Mardi Gras, Parade in New Orleans in 1977; the theme was "Happily Ever After".

Winkler said he was named after his Uncle Helmut, who did not make it out of German during World War II.<ref name=EmmyTVLegends-Interview-2006 /> His middle name, Franklin, was in honor of President [[Franklin D. Roosevelt]].<ref name=EmmyTVLegends-Interview-2006 />

Winkler has the learning disability, [[dyslexia]], which he was not diagnosed with until the age of 31.<ref name=Guardian-Zipzer-2014 />

He is an avid [[fly fisherman]], which he often does in [[Montana]]. On the rewards of this hobby, Winker said: " The repetition of it, the sound of the water, I find it to be totally draining. Anything that bothers you is completely washed from your body. I see fly-fishing as a washing machine for your brain. My technique is still ugly as sin. But somehow I get the fish."<ref name=HReporter-RoyalPainsSecrets-2011 />

